	 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;u&gt;Drinking water&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		We encourage and support children to drink throughout the day.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Children (and staff) have access to drinking water at all times throughout the day. Children can independently serve themselves using the jug and disposable water cups available inside and water fountains outside/cups and jug. The jug is filled for the beginning of the session and re-filled as and when needed which is sterilized at the end of the day. Children also have a drink at snack and at lunch.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;u&gt;Curriculum&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		As part of the curriculum we discuss healthy practices, including the need to drink water after physical exercise, hot weather.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		We also discuss healthy eating. We help children to understand why some foods are healthy and others are not.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;
		Children participate in cooking activities and gardening. They try foods from a range of cultures (respecting parental views and taking into consideration children&amp;rsquo;s dietary requirements).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Policy Last Updated: September 2013&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;&gt;
	 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;&gt;
	 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;&gt;
	 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	  &lt;/p&gt;</content>
	</entry>
	<entry>
		<title>If you have a concern</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="/early-years/early-years-policies/53-if-you-have-a-concern.html"/>
		<published>2010-08-29T15:18:40Z</published>
		<updated>2010-08-29T15:18:40Z</updated>
		<id>https://westwardschool.co.uk/early-years/early-years-policies/53-if-you-have-a-concern.html</id>
		<author>
			<name>Mrs Stevenson</name>
		<email>westwardschool@btconnect.com</email>
		</author>
		<summary type="html">&lt;h2 style=&quot;text-align: center&quot;&gt;
	What to do if you have a concern about your child&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;
	 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	All parents will have queries and concerns about their child&amp;rsquo;s experiences/learning at school from time to time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	However small an issue we are always here to help.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The Westward Home Message Book is your link to us in school so please do use it to ask the teacher any questions or tell us about your concerns.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	All Home Message Books are read and replied to on a daily basis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Alternatively if you feel you would like to come in to speak privately to the teacher then do ask for a meeting which will be arranged at the nearest possible convenient time for both parent and teacher.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	If your concern is about meal times and food then Mrs James the School Manager is available to speak to by phone during the day in the school office or at the front door every morning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	We always try to deal with concerns and queries as quickly and as smoothly as we can.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	If you are a working parent who can&amp;rsquo;t easily get to school then we will find a convenient time to meet. Most teachers are in school from very early in the morning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	You may also email the school office with any queries or concerns.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&lt;span class=&quot;scayt-misspell&quot; data-scayt_word=&quot;Headteacher&quot; data-scaytid=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Headteacher&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Mrs Stevenson&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	  &lt;/p&gt;</summary>
		<content type="html">&lt;h2 style=&quot;text-align: center&quot;&gt;
	What to do if you have a concern about your child&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;
	 &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	All parents will have queries and concerns about their child&amp;rsquo;s experiences/learning at school from time to time.&lt;/p&gt;
